race.comment: Tricky little race. ESHA (1) resumes. She made waves with two fast wins over 1000m which saw her thrown in the deep end in a G1 Moir Stakes at her third ever start, sent out a $6.50 chance. She had a few issues there and can be forgiven for the pre-spell miss, if she's back to her best she'll be very hard to catch but 60kg and 1100m are niggles. Wary of MILITARY TYCOON (2) who resumes. Her fresh win in the G3 Ottawa Stakes here last time in was very good and she was hardly disgraced in a Golden Slipper or Percy Sykes (behind Tempted) her next couple. JENNI THE NINJA (8) won in good time on debut at Pakenham over 1000m and can only improve. She should measure up. CONSCIENCE (6) resumes having shown good ability. She's right in the mix ahead of ROSANGELA (12) who won her maiden well last time.
